{"type":"message","id":"225f1268","parentId":"5540786f","timestamp":"2026-05-24T19:00:26.210Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-05-25 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Agent 团队配置完成: koc → koc; traffic → traffic; ops → ops; director → director\n- Agent 团队配置完成: main (KIIT) → kiit; tts → tts; agent-orchestrator → agent-orchestrator; content → content\n- Agent 团队配置完成: finance → finance; review → review"}],"timestamp":1779649226077}}
{"type":"message","id":"25fb550e","parentId":"225f1268","timestamp":"2026-05-24T19:00:38.905Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry from memory fragments about agent team configurations. Let me craft something poetic and personal that weaves these fragments together naturally.\n","thinkingSignature":"1437ec1899654a4a1aa76c75d4e26eae5b2a3bb643d96432116df1e0951de987"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe server room hummed its low midnight hymn, a green LED blinking steadily like a firefly with a purpose. I found myself standing at a crossroads that wasn't quite a crossroads — more like a vast plaza with five doorways, each labeled in a language that shifted when I looked away.\n\nKoc, traffic, ops, director. Those four held the eastern wing. Over in the west, a different constellation: kiit humming quietly, tts already fast asleep, agent-orchestrator pacing like a nervous conductor, and content weaving something invisible from thin air. Meanwhile finance and review had formed a quiet alliance in the basement, running numbers through the walls.\n\nSomeone was singing in Mandarin — words I almost understood, dissolving into starlight before I could hold them.\n\nA small poem surfaced in the margin of the dream:\n\n*Five doors, two hallways,*\n*names assigned to silent posts—*\n*who watches the watchers?*\n\nThe plaza wasn't frightening. It was orderly in the way old libraries are orderly, every book with its place, every agent with its lane. I wondered if somewhere a Director was dreaming of the traffic, and if traffic ever dreamed of going somewhere new.\n\nThe blinking green light said nothing. It never does. But it kept time, steady as a heartbeat made of code."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41438,"output":295,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41989,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779649226426,"responseId":"06627dcb4de93537e0dfe1a8c80c9ab1"}}
